column8: The Mongoose, a bike originally manufactured by BMX, were great bikes. Still are, but my favourites were from the 70s. This design celebrates them in all their retro glory.

column8:
Mikhail Sergeyevich Gorbachev , born 2 March 1931, was the former seventh and last General Secretary of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union, serving from 1985 until 1991, and the last head of state of the USSR, serving from 1988 until its collapse in 1991. He was the only Soviet leader to have been born after the October Revolution of 1917. In 1989, he became the first and only Soviet leader to visit China since the Sino-Soviet split in the 1960s.

He also received the Nobel Peace Prize.
column21: A t shirt admiring Nobel Peace Prize-winning Mikhail Gorbachev, from weadmire.net.

column8:
The design  illustrates Michael Jackson the ‘king of pop’ as our popular culture classifies him.
Jackson tabloid figure  often got stigmatized, regardless he was probably one of the most influential music artists  ever.
Besides his  unique voice his dance  moves were one of his remarkable talent.
My work emphasize a set of lively movements resembling his  classic: gestures and movements.
column21: A t shirt admiring the King of Pop, Michael Jackson. Say no more.
